==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Minder
<hw>Mind"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
minds, tends, or watches something, as a child, a machine, or cattle;
<as>as, a <ex>minder</ex> of a loom</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One to be attended; specif., a pauper child
intrusted to the care of a private person.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mindful</ent>⟦br⟧
